{"word":"εὐερκής","slug":"εὐερκής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐερκής</b></el> <el>(εὐ-ερκής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἕρκος'><el>ἕρκος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>well-fenced, well-walled</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>fencing well, well-closed</i>, of doors, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}